  "prompt": "What countries have extradition treaties with UAE?",
  "response": "The United Arab Emirates (UAE) has entered into extradition treaties with numerous countries worldwide. While the specific list can change over time as new treaties are signed or existing ones are modified, the UAE has typically established extradition agreements with countries including, but not limited to:\n\n1. United States\n2. United Kingdom\n3. Canada\n4. India\n5. Australia\n6. France\n7. Germany\n8. Italy\n9. China\n10. Pakistan\n11. Saudi Arabia\n12. Egypt\n\nThese treaties generally facilitate the process of extraditing individuals accused or convicted of crimes across borders to face justice. It's important to note that the terms and conditions of these treaties can vary, including the types of crimes covered and any legal protections or exceptions. For the most current and specific information, you should consult official government sources or legal experts in international law.",
